Name: (V48) DAP Data Load
checklistText:
<size=21>(V48) CSM - DAP Data Load Procedure (R03)</size>

1.
	Key V48E 

2.
	FL V04 N46
		R1: A B C D E
		R2: A B C D E

Register 1
A: What is the configuration:
	A = 0 - No DAP
	A = 1 - CSM
	A = 2 - CSM & LM
	A = 3 - CSM & SIVB
	A = 6 - CSM & LM Ascent Stage Only 

B: QUAD A/C FOR X
	B = 0 - Fail A/C 
	B = 1 - Use A/C 

C: QUAD B/D FOR X
	C = 0 - Fail B/D 
	C = 1 - Use B/D 

D: ERR DEADBAND
	D = 0 - Attitude deadband 0.5 degrees 
	D = 1 - Attitude deadband 5.0 degrees

E: RATE SELECT
	E = 0 - 0.05 deg/sec 
	E = 1 - 0.2 deg/sec
	E = 2 - 0.5 deg/sec
	E = 3 - 2.0 deg/sec 

Register 2
A = ROLL QUAD SELECT
	A = 0 - USE B/C
	A = 1 - USE A/C

B: QUAD A
	B = 0 - Fail 
	B = 1 - Use
 
C: QUAD B
	C = 0 - Fail 
	C = 1 - Use 
 
D: QUAD C
	D = 0 - Fail 
	D = 1 - Use 
 
E: QUAD D
	E = 0 - Fail 
	E = 1 - Use 

Accept: Key PRO 
Reject: Key V21, V22, or V24 - Load desired DAP data code and/or channel 30 back-up code 

3.
FL V06 N47 
	R1: CSM weight 			XXXXX lb 
	R2: LM weight 			XXXXX lb 


Accept:	Key PRO - If DPS has been staged, exit RO3
Reject: 	Key V21E, V22E, or V24E
		Load Correct Data

4.
FL V06 N48
	R1: P Trim				XXX.XX deg
	R2: Y Trim				XXX.XX deg

Accept:	PRO - Return to prog
Reject: 	Key V21E, V22E, or V24E
		Load Correct Data

5.	To activate DAP
Panel 1:
	CMC MODE - FREE
	Key V49E
